        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 10:03PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1002 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over South Thompson, or 8
miles south of Lyons. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Rainfall totals of 2 to 4 inches have occurred in the last 2
hours this may lead to areas of localized flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding especially
in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Vidalia, Uvalda, Alston, South Thompson, Center, Toombs Central, New
Branch, Rock Springs, Cedar Crossing, and Johnson Corner.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.  Electrical
appliances should not be used unless in an emergency. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
